    "Finding the vertex of a parabola. Verifying solutions to quadratic equations. Converting to forms for specific uses like optimization problems.": "Finding the 顶点 of a 抛物线. Verifying 解 to quadratic equations. Converting to forms 对于 specific uses like optimization problems.",
    "First, identify first term a and common ratio r. Check |r|": "First, identify first term a and common ratio r. Check |r|",
    "For a + bi, the conjugate is a - bi. When a polynomial with real coefficients has a complex zero, its conjugate is also a zero. Complex zeros come in conjugate pairs.": "对于 a + bi, the conjugate is a - bi. 当 a 多项式 with 实数 coefficients has a 复杂 零, its conjugate is also a 零. 复杂 zeros come in conjugate pairs.",
    "For ax² + bx + c, find two numbers that multiply to ac and add to b. Use these to split the middle term, then factor by grouping. Alternatively, use the AC method.": "对于 ax² + bx + c, find two numbers that 乘 to ac and 加 to b. Use these to split the middle term, 那么 因式分解 by grouping. Alternatively, use the AC 方法.",
    "For equations like A/B = C/D, cross-multiply: AD = BC. This shortcut is valid and often simpler than finding LCD, but still check for extraneous solutions.": "对于 equations like A/B = C/D, cross-乘: AD = BC. This shortcut is valid and often simpler than finding LCD, but still check 对于 extraneous 解.",
    "For n(x)/d(x) where deg(n) = deg(d) + 1, divide to get quotient q(x) + remainder. The asymptote is y = q(x). As x → ±∞, the function approaches this line.": "对于 n(x)/d(x) 其中 deg(n) = deg(d) + 1, 除 to get quotient q(x) + remainder. The 渐近线 is y = q(x). As x → ±∞, the 函数 approaches this line.",
    "For polynomial p(x) with integer coefficients, any rational root p/q (in lowest terms) has p dividing the constant term and q dividing the leading coefficient. This narrows possible rational zeros significantly.": "对于 多项式 p(x) with integer coefficients, any 有理 root p/q (in lowest terms) has p dividing the 常数 term and q dividing the leading coefficient. This narrows possible 有理 zeros significantly.",
    "Form a + bi where a and b are real and i² = -1. Real part is a, imaginary part is b. Complex numbers extend our number system to allow nth roots of any polynomial.": "Form a + bi 其中 a and b are 实数 and i² = -1. 实数 part is a, imaginary part is b. 复杂 numbers extend our number system to allow nth roots of any 多项式.",
    "Form f(x) = ab^x where a ≠ 0, b > 0, b ≠ 1. Base b determines growth (b > 1) or decay (0": "Form f(x) = ab^x 其中 a ≠ 0, b > 0, b ≠ 1. Base b determines 增长 (b > 1) or 衰减 (0",
    "Fractions with fractions in numerator/denominator. Simplify by finding LCM of all denominators and multiplying numerator and denominator by it. Or treat numerator and denominator separately, simplify, then divide.": "Fractions with fractions in 分子/分母. 简化 by finding LCM of all denominators and multiplying 分子 and 分母 by it. Or treat 分子 and 分母 separately, 简化, 那么 除.",
    "Fractions with polynomials in numerator and denominator. Form P(x)/Q(x) where Q(x) ≠ 0. Domain excludes values making the denominator zero (restrictions).": "Fractions with polynomials in 分子 and 分母. Form P(x)/Q(x) 其中 Q(x) ≠ 0. 定义域 excludes values making the 分母 零 (restrictions).",
    "Full rotation = 360°. Right angle = 90°. Straight angle = 180°. Acute angle": "Full rotation = 360°. Right angle = 90°. Straight angle = 180°. Acute angle",
