    "Line: r(t) = r₀ + tv (parametric form). Projectile motion: r(t) = (vcos α)t i + ((vsin α)t - ½gt²) j. Work: W = F·d. Physics problems model forces and motion as vectors.": "Line: r(t) = r₀ + tv (parametric form). Projectile motion: r(t) = (vcos α)t i + ((vsin α)t - ½gt²) j. Work: W = F·d. Physics problems model forces and motion as vectors.",
    "Linear Inequalities:": "Linear Inequalities:",
    "Linear functions grow fastest for small x, but exponential eventually dominates. Logarithmic functions grow slowest. For very large x: exponential > linear > logarithmic.": "Linear functions grow fastest 对于 small x, but exponential eventually dominates. Logarithmic functions grow slowest. 对于 very large x: exponential > linear > logarithmic.",
    "Linear patterns in data. Counting: total items in stepped arrangement. Time intervals: events at regular intervals. Savings plans: deposit fixed amount each period.": "Linear patterns in data. Counting: total items in stepped arrangement. Time intervals: events at regular intervals. Savings plans: deposit fixed amount each period.",
    "Linear programming and system optimization appear in AP Calculus as constrained optimization and Lagrange multipliers. Understanding these foundations is essential for advanced mathematics.": "Linear programming and system optimization appear in AP Calculus as constrained optimization and Lagrange multipliers. Understanding these foundations is essential 对于 advanced mathematics.",
    "Linearity (relationship is linear), independence (observations independent), normality (residuals approximately normal), equal variance (residuals have constant spread for all x).": "Linearity (relationship is linear), independence (observations independent), normality (residuals approximately normal), equal variance (residuals have 常数 spread 对于 all x).",
    "List all factors of the constant term and leading coefficient. Form possible rational roots. Test each using synthetic division (or p(c) = 0). This is efficient for polynomials degree 3 and higher.": "List all factors of the 常数 term and leading coefficient. Form possible 有理 roots. Test each using synthetic division (or p(c) = 0). This is efficient 对于 polynomials 度 3 and higher.",
    "Loan amortization uses series formulas. Monthly payment computed using present value of annuity. Stock dividend accumulation. Pendulum oscillation amplitudes (geometric decay). Recursive sequences define many real systems.": "Loan amortization uses 级数 formulas. Monthly payment computed using present value of annuity. Stock dividend accumulation. Pendulum oscillation amplitudes (几何 衰减). Recursive sequences define many 实数 systems.",
