    "Making Coefficients Opposite:": "Making Coefficients Opposite:",
    "Many problems use C(n,r) to count favorable outcomes. Example: probability of 2 heads in 3 coin flips: C(3,2)/2^3 = 3/8. Lottery odds: C(49,6) total combinations.": "Many problems use C(n,r) to count favorable outcomes. 例子: probability of 2 heads in 3 coin flips: C(3,2)/2^3 = 3/8. Lottery odds: C(49,6) total combinations.",
    "Mark the boundary point. Shade left of the point if x < or x ≤, right if x > or x ≥. Use open circle for strict inequalities, closed for ≤/≥.": "Mark the boundary point. Shade left of the point 如果 x < or x ≤, right 如果 x > or x ≥. Use open 圆 对于 strict inequalities, closed 对于 ≤/≥.",
    "Mark the roots on a number line. Test one x-value in each interval in the original inequality. If true, the entire interval is part of the solution. If false, the interval is excluded.": "Mark the roots on a number line. Test one x-value in each interval in the original inequality. 如果 true, the entire interval is part of the 解. 如果 false, the interval is excluded.",
    "Mathematical Induction:": "Mathematical Induction:",
    "Mathematical induction foundation for many calculus proofs and theorem verification. Recursive functions and sequences central to analysis. The principle of induction connects to the completeness axiom in real number system, essential for rigorous calculus development.": "Mathematical induction foundation 对于 many calculus proofs and 定理 verification. Recursive functions and sequences central to analysis. The principle of induction connects to the completeness axiom in 实数 number system, essential 对于 rigorous calculus development.",
    "Mean = 0, standard deviation = 1. Denoted Z ~ N(0,1). Z-table gives cumulative probability P(Z ≤ z). Any normal random variable can be converted to standard form: Z = (X - μ)/σ.": "Mean = 0, standard deviation = 1. Denoted Z ~ N(0,1). Z-table gives cumulative probability P(Z ≤ z). Any normal random variable can be converted to standard form: Z = (X - μ)/σ.",
    "Medical diagnosis: likelihood of disease given test result. Quality control: probability defective given supplier. Database queries: probability matching criteria given constraints.": "Medical diagnosis: likelihood of disease given test result. Quality control: probability defective given supplier. Database queries: probability matching criteria given constraints.",
    "Mixture problems:": "Mixture problems:",
    "Models like P(x) = kx/(1 + ax) where productivity increases then levels off. The horizontal asymptote k/a represents maximum productivity as x → ∞.": "Models like P(x) = kx/(1 + ax) 其中 productivity increases 那么 levels off. The horizontal 渐近线 k/a 表示 maximum productivity as x → ∞.",
    "Multiplication & Division in Polar Form:": "Multiplication & Division in Polar Form:",
