    "P(A|B) = P(B|A) · P(A) / P(B). Relates conditional probabilities in both directions. Used in medical testing: P(disease|positive test) involves test accuracy.": "P(A|B) = P(B|A) · P(A) / P(B). Relates conditional probabilities in both directions. Used in medical testing: P(disease|正数 test) involves test accuracy.",
    "P(X ≤ a) requires standardizing to Z, then using table. P(a": "P(X ≤ a) requires standardizing to Z, 那么 using table. P(a",
    "P(event) = (favorable outcomes)/(total outcomes) for equally likely outcomes. Ranges from 0 (impossible) to 1 (certain). 0% to 100%. Complement rule: P(not A) = 1 - P(A).": "P(event) = (favorable outcomes)/(total outcomes) 对于 equally likely outcomes. Ranges from 0 (impossible) to 1 (certain). 0% to 100%. Complement rule: P(not A) = 1 - P(A).",
    "P(t) = P_0 e^{rt} (continuous) or P(t) = P_0(1+r)^t (discrete). r is growth rate. Doubling time: 0.693/r (continuous). Applications: bacteria, human population, viral spread.": "P(t) = P_0 e^{rt} (continuous) or P(t) = P_0(1+r)^t (discrete). r is 增长 rate. Doubling time: 0.693/r (continuous). Applications: bacteria, human population, viral spread.",
    "P(x)/Q(x) and [P(x) × R(x)]/[Q(x) × R(x)] are equivalent rational expressions (same domain restrictions). Use this to find common denominators or create equivalent forms.": "P(x)/Q(x) and [P(x) × R(x)]/[Q(x) × R(x)] are equivalent 有理 expressions (same 定义域 restrictions). Use this to find common denominators or create equivalent forms.",
    "Parabola & Hyperbola:": "抛物线 & 双曲线:",
    "Parabola: (y-k)² = 4p(x-h) (horizontal) or (x-h)² = 4p(y-k) (vertical). Vertex (h, k), focus, directrix p units away. Hyperbola: (x-h)²/a² - (y-k)²/b² = 1 (horizontal) or reversed. Asymptotes: y - k = ±(b/a)(x - h). Eccentricity e = c/a > 1 where c² = a² + b².": "抛物线: (y-k)² = 4p(x-h) (horizontal) or (x-h)² = 4p(y-k) (vertical). 顶点 (h, k), focus, 准线 p units away. 双曲线: (x-h)²/a² - (y-k)²/b² = 1 (horizontal) or reversed. Asymptotes: y - k = ±(b/a)(x - h). Eccentricity e = c/a > 1 其中 c² = a² + b².",
    "Parametric Representation:": "Parametric Representation:",
    "Passes through (1, 0) because log_b(1) = 0. Passes through (b, 1) because log_b(b) = 1. Increasing if b > 1, decreasing if 0": "Passes through (1, 0) because log_b(1) = 0. Passes through (b, 1) because log_b(b) = 1. Increasing 如果 b > 1, decreasing 如果 0",
    "Passwords: each position could be different letter/digit. Seating arrangements. Top finishers in race. Anagrams of words (with and without repeated letters).": "Passwords: each position could be different letter/digit. Seating arrangements. Top finishers in race. Anagrams of words (with and without repeated letters).",
    "Perfect Square Trinomials:": "Perfect 平方 Trinomials:",
    "Perfect square trinomials: a² + 2ab + b² = (a+b)². Sum/difference of cubes: a³ + b³ = (a+b)(a²-ab+b²). Factoring by grouping for four-term polynomials.": "Perfect 平方 trinomials: a² + 2ab + b² = (a+b)². 和/difference of cubes: a³ + b³ = (a+b)(a²-ab+b²). Factoring by grouping 对于 four-term polynomials.",
    "Perimeter problems that lead to area quadratics. Garden fence problems: find dimensions that maximize area with fixed perimeter. Area = length × width, then substitute using the constraint.": "Perimeter problems that lead to area quadratics. Garden fence problems: find dimensions that maximize area with fixed perimeter. Area = length × width, 那么 substitute using the constraint.",
    "Periodicity & Signs:": "Periodicity & Signs:",
    "Permutations:": "Permutations:",
    "Pick a test point in the shaded region to verify it satisfies both inequalities. The entire shaded region represents the solution set.": "Pick a test point in the shaded region to verify it satisfies both inequalities. The entire shaded region 表示 the 解 set.",
    "Plot the vertex and axis of symmetry first. Plot the y-intercept and its symmetric point. Find and plot x-intercepts if they exist. Use the shape (determined by a) to sketch a smooth U or inverted-U curve.": "Plot the 顶点 and 轴 of 对称 first. Plot the y-intercept and its symmetric point. Find and plot x-intercepts 如果 they exist. Use the shape (determined by a) to sketch a smooth U or inverted-U curve.",
    "Plot the y-intercept, then use slope to find another point. Slope indicates rise over run: positive slopes go ↗, negative slopes go ↘.": "Plot the y-intercept, 那么 use slope to find another point. Slope indicates rise over run: 正数 slopes go ↗, 负数 slopes go ↘.",
