    "Prepare to learn substitution and elimination methods in the next lessons. Both methods transform the system to isolate variables and find the solution.": "Prepare to learn 代入 and 消元 methods in the next lessons. Both methods transform the system to isolate variables and find the 解.",
    "Probability Definition:": "Probability Definition:",
    "Probability with Combinations:": "Probability with Combinations:",
    "Product: z₁z₂ = r₁r₂ cis(θ₁ + θ₂). Quotient: z₁/z₂ = (r₁/r₂) cis(θ₁ - θ₂). Real and imaginary parts multiply in polar but angles add/subtract.": "Product: z₁z₂ = r₁r₂ cis(θ₁ + θ₂). Quotient: z₁/z₂ = (r₁/r₂) cis(θ₁ - θ₂). 实数 and imaginary parts 乘 in polar but angles 加/减.",
    "Productivity and Diminishing Returns:": "Productivity and Diminishing Returns:",
    "Profit P(x) = Revenue - Cost = R(x) - C(x). Often quadratic. Find maximum profit at the vertex. Break-even points are where P(x) = 0 (setting revenue equal to cost).": "Profit P(x) = Revenue - Cost = R(x) - C(x). Often quadratic. Find maximum profit at the 顶点. Break-even points are 其中 P(x) = 0 (setting revenue equal to cost).",
    "Profit and Revenue:": "Profit and Revenue:",
    "Projectile Motion:": "Projectile Motion:",
    "Projectile motion: x(t) = v₀cos θ·t, y(t) = v₀sin θ·t - ½gt². Cycloid: x = r(t - sin t), y = r(1 - cos t). Parametric curves used extensively in physics and calculus for motion analysis.": "Projectile motion: x(t) = v₀cos θ·t, y(t) = v₀sin θ·t - ½gt². Cycloid: x = r(t - sin t), y = r(1 - cos t). Parametric curves used extensively in physics and calculus 对于 motion analysis.",
    "Proof technique for statements about all positive integers. Two steps: (1) Base case: prove statement true for n = 1. (2) Inductive step: assume true for n = k, prove it's true for n = k+1. Proves infinitely many cases with finite work.": "Proof technique 对于 statements about all 正数 integers. Two steps: (1) Base case: prove statement true 对于 n = 1. (2) Inductive 步骤: assume true 对于 n = k, prove it's true 对于 n = k+1. Proves infinitely many cases with finite work.",
    "Properties of Exponents:": "Properties of Exponents:",
    "Prove Σ_{i=1}^{n} i = n(n+1)/2. Prove geometric sequence formula a_n = a_1 · r^{n-1}. Prove statements about divisibility: 3^n - 1 is always divisible by 2.": "Prove Σ_{i=1}^{n} i = n(n+1)/2. Prove 几何 数列 公式 a_n = a_1 · r^{n-1}. Prove statements about divisibility: 3^n - 1 is always divisible by 2.",
    "Quadratic Functions:": "Quadratic Functions:",
    "Quotient has degree one less than the dividend. If remainder is 0, (x-c) is a factor. If remainder is non-zero, R(x) = R and result is Q(x) + R/(x-c).": "Quotient has 度 one 小于 the dividend. 如果 remainder is 0, (x-c) is a 因式分解. 如果 remainder is non-零, R(x) = R and result is Q(x) + R/(x-c).",
    "Radian Measure:": "弧度 Measure:",
    "Radioactive Decay:": "Radioactive 衰减:",
    "Radioactive decay: N(t) = N_0 e^{-μt}. Half-life calculation when N(t) = N_0/2. pH in chemistry: pH = -log[H⁺]. Earthquake magnitude: M = log(I/I_0).": "Radioactive 衰减: N(t) = N_0 e^{-μt}. 半衰期 calculation 当 N(t) = N_0/2. pH in chemistry: pH = -log[H⁺]. Earthquake magnitude: M = log(I/I_0).",
    "Range estimate for population parameter. 95% confidence interval means 95% of such intervals would contain true parameter. General formula: estimate ± (critical value) × (standard error). For mean: x̄ ± t* × s/√n.": "值域 estimate 对于 population parameter. 95% confidence interval means 95% of such intervals would contain true parameter. General 公式: estimate ± (critical value) × (standard error). 对于 mean: x̄ ± t* × s/√n.",
    "Rational Expressions:": "有理 Expressions:",
    "Rational Root Theorem:": "有理 Root 定理:",
    "Rational functions appear in optimization problems (minimize cost, maximize profit). L'Hôpital's Rule in calculus uses these to evaluate limits. Partial fraction decomposition is used for integration.": "有理 functions appear in optimization problems (minimize cost, maximize profit). L'Hôpital's Rule in calculus uses these to evaluate limits. Partial fraction decomposition is used 对于 integration.",
