    "Regression Line Equation:": "Regression Line Equation:",
    "Regression inference (confidence intervals, hypothesis tests) are central to AP Statistics. Understanding sampling distributions of estimators connects to calculus-based probability and limits. LOWESS regression and smoothing lead to advanced statistical methods.": "Regression inference (confidence intervals, hypothesis tests) are central to AP Statistics. Understanding sampling distributions of estimators connects to calculus-based probability and limits. LOWESS regression and smoothing lead to advanced statistical methods.",
    "Removable:": "Removable:",
    "Repeating decimals to fractions. Fractal areas and lengths (Koch snowflake). Loan and mortgage calculations using present value. Annuities and perpetuities in finance.": "Repeating decimals to fractions. Fractal areas and lengths (Koch snowflake). Loan and mortgage calculations using present value. Annuities and perpetuities in finance.",
    "S_n = (n/2)(a_1 + a_n) = (n/2)(2a_1 + (n-1)d). Gauss's formula: sum of first n positive integers is n(n+1)/2. Sum is always the average of first and last term, times the count.": "S_n = (n/2)(a_1 + a_n) = (n/2)(2a_1 + (n-1)d). Gauss's 公式: 和 of first n 正数 integers is n(n+1)/2. 和 is always the average of first and last term, times the count.",
    "Sample Space & Events:": "Sample Space & Events:",
    "Sample space is all possible outcomes. Event is subset of sample space. Experiment can produce random outcomes. Example: die roll has sample space {1,2,3,4,5,6}.": "Sample space is all possible outcomes. Event is subset of sample space. Experiment can produce random outcomes. 例子: die roll has sample space {1,2,3,4,5,6}.",
    "Selection of objects where ORDER DOESN'T MATTER. C(n,r) = n!/(r!(n-r)!), also written \"n choose r\". Always C(n,r) ≤ P(n,r). Example: choosing 3 of 5 books: C(5,3) = 5!/(3!2!) = 10.": "Selection of objects 其中 ORDER DOESN'T MATTER. C(n,r) = n!/(r!(n-r)!), also written \"n choose r\". Always C(n,r) ≤ P(n,r). 例子: choosing 3 of 5 books: C(5,3) = 5!/(3!2!) = 10.",
    "Sequence with constant difference d between consecutive terms. a_n = a_1 + (n-1)d. Example: 2, 5, 8, 11, 14... has a_1 = 2, d = 3. The common difference can be negative or zero.": "数列 with 常数 difference d between consecutive terms. a_n = a_1 + (n-1)d. 例子: 2, 5, 8, 11, 14... has a_1 = 2, d = 3. The common difference can be 负数 or 零.",
    "Sequence with constant ratio r between consecutive terms. a_n = a_1 · r^{n-1}. Example: 2, 6, 18, 54... has a_1 = 2, r = 3. Each term is r times the previous term.": "数列 with 常数 ratio r between consecutive terms. a_n = a_1 · r^{n-1}. 例子: 2, 6, 18, 54... has a_1 = 2, r = 3. Each term is r times the previous term.",
    "Series where consecutive terms cancel: Σ (a_i - a_{i+1}) = a_1 - a_{n+1}. Useful for partial fractions decomposition.": "级数 其中 consecutive terms cancel: Σ (a_i - a_{i+1}) = a_1 - a_{n+1}. Useful 对于 partial fractions decomposition.",
