    "T(t) = T_s + (T_0 - T_s)e^{-kt} describes temperature decrease. T_s is surrounding temperature, T_0 is initial temperature, k is cooling rate. Temperature approaches T_s asymptotically.": "T(t) = T_s + (T_0 - T_s)e^{-kt} 描述 temperature decrease. T_s is surrounding temperature, T_0 is initial temperature, k is cooling rate. Temperature approaches T_s asymptotically.",
