    "The Substitution Method:": "The 代入 方法:",
    "The domain is the set of all possible input values, while the range is the set of all possible output values. Restrictions occur when denominators are zero or when values are under even-root radicals.": "The 定义域 是...的集合 all possible 输入 values, while the 值域 是...的集合 all possible 输出 values. 限制发生在 当 denominators are 零 or 当 values are under even-root radicals.",
    "The maximum or minimum occurs at a corner point (vertex) of the feasible region. Find all vertices and test each in the objective function.": "The maximum or minimum 发生在 a corner point (顶点) of the feasible region. Find all vertices and test each in the objective 函数.",
    "The vertex is the turning point. The axis of symmetry is the vertical line x = -b/(2a) passing through the vertex. The parabola is symmetric about this line.": "The 顶点 is the turning point. The 轴 of 对称 is the vertical line x = -b/(2a) passing through the 顶点. The 抛物线 is symmetric about this line.",
    "These theorems avoid long division. Instead of dividing p(x) by (x-c), calculate p(c) directly. If p(c) = 0, we know (x-c) divides evenly.": "These theorems avoid long division. Instead of dividing p(x) by (x-c), calculate p(c) directly. 如果 p(c) = 0, we know (x-c) divides evenly.",
    "This method works best when one variable has a coefficient of 1 or -1, making it easy to isolate. If all coefficients are complex, elimination might be easier.": "This 方法 works best 当 one variable has a coefficient of 1 or -1, making it easy to isolate. 如果 all coefficients are 复杂, 消元 might be easier.",
    "Three-Variable Systems:": "Three-Variable Systems:",
    "Time required for quantity to reduce to half its value. After one half-life, 50% remains. After two half-lives, 25% remains (50% of 50%). n half-lives: (1/2)^n fraction remains.": "Time required 对于 quantity to reduce to half its value. After one 半衰期, 50% remains. After two half-lives, 25% remains (50% of 50%). n half-lives: (1/2)^n fraction remains.",
    "Transformations:": "Transformations:",
    "Trigonometric Ratios:": "Trigonometric Ratios:",
    "Trigonometric functions are periodic. Derivatives: d/dx(sin x) = cos x, d/dx(cos x) = -sin x. Integration of sin/cos appears throughout calculus. Exponential and trig connection via Euler's formula: e^{iθ} = cos θ + i sin θ.": "Trigonometric functions are periodic. Derivatives: d/dx(sin x) = cos x, d/dx(cos x) = -sin x. Integration of sin/cos appears throughout calculus. Exponential and trig connection via Euler's 公式: e^{iθ} = cos θ + i sin θ.",
    "Trigonometric functions repeat every 2π radians. Signs vary by quadrant: Q1 all positive, Q2 sin positive, Q3 tan positive, Q4 cos positive.": "Trigonometric functions repeat every 2π 弧度. Signs vary by quadrant: Q1 all 正数, Q2 sin 正数, Q3 tan 正数, Q4 cos 正数.",
