    "When 0": "当 0",
    "When b > 1, f(x) = ab^x grows exponentially. The larger b, the faster the growth. Doubling time or tripling time describes how long for the function to double or triple in value.": "当 b > 1, f(x) = ab^x grows exponentially. The larger b, the faster the 增长. Doubling time or tripling time 描述 how long 对于 the 函数 to double or triple in value.",
    "When clearing denominators, we might introduce solutions that make the original denominator zero. These are extraneous. Always verify: substitute back and check if any denominator becomes zero.": "当 clearing denominators, we might introduce 解 that make the original 分母 零. These are extraneous. Always verify: substitute back and check 如果 any 分母 becomes 零.",
    "When polynomial p(x) is divided by (x-c), the remainder equals p(c). This allows quick evaluation: instead of substituting into a complex polynomial, perform synthetic division and read the remainder.": "当 多项式 p(x) is divided by (x-c), the remainder 等于 p(c). This allows quick evaluation: instead of substituting into a 复杂 多项式, perform synthetic division and read the remainder.",
